_exptl_crystal_grow.pdbx_details    
;BATCH, 1.51 M MGSO4 . 7 H2O, 0.59 MM TRYPSIN, 1.0 MM ZN(II) 5.0 % DMSO: 
CRYSTALLIZATION SOLUTION WAS SATURATED IN KETO-BABIM. CRYSTAL WAS TRANSFERRED 
TO SYNTHETIC MOTHER LIQUOR CONTAINING 2.11 M ZN(II), PH 3.85 AND SOAKED FOR 
SEVERAL DAYS WITH SEVERAL REPLACEMENTS OF SOAKING SOLUTIONS. THE SOLUTION WAS 
SATURATED IN KETO-BABIM AND CONTAINED 2.0 % DMSO TO INCREASE INHIBITOR 
SOLUBILITY. UNDER THIS CONDITION KETO-BABIM UNDERGOES DECOMPOSITION TO 5- 
AMIDINO-BENZIMIDAZOLE.
;
